abstract: China will make good on a pledge to purchase more than $40 billion per year of U.S. agricultural products under the recently agreed Phase 1 trade deal between the two countries, China's top agriculture consultancy said on Friday.
snippet: China will make good on a pledge to purchase more than $40 billion per year of U.S. agricultural products under the recently agreed Phase 1 trade deal between the two countries, China's top agriculture consultancy said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China will make good on a pledge to purchase more than $40 billion per year of U.S. agricultural products under the recently agreed Phase 1 trade deal between the two countries, China's top agriculture consultancy said on Friday.
headline_main: China Can Fulfil $40 Billion U.S. Farm Purchase Pledge: Consultancy
headline_print_headline: China Can Fulfil $40 Billion U.S. Farm Purchase Pledge: Consultancy

abstract: Britain's new government named Andrew Bailey as the Bank of England's next boss on Friday, entrusting a veteran regulator and technocrat with steering the economy and its vast finance industry through Brexit.
snippet: Britain's new government named Andrew Bailey as the Bank of England's next boss on Friday, entrusting a veteran regulator and technocrat with steering the economy and its vast finance industry through Brexit.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain's new government named Andrew Bailey as the Bank of England's next boss on Friday, entrusting a veteran regulator and technocrat with steering the economy and its vast finance industry through Brexit.
headline_main: Veteran Watchdog Bailey to Guide Bank of England Through Brexit
headline_print_headline: Veteran Watchdog Bailey to Guide Bank of England Through Brexit

abstract: Volkswagen AG took two raps in Australia on Friday as a court slapped a A$125 million (£66.09 million) fine on the German car maker as part of a global emissions cheating scandal and a regulator launched a civil lawsuit against a unit.
snippet: Volkswagen AG took two raps in Australia on Friday as a court slapped a A$125 million (£66.09 million) fine on the German car maker as part of a global emissions cheating scandal and a regulator launched a civil lawsuit against a unit.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Volkswagen AG took two raps in Australia on Friday as a court slapped a A$125 million (£66.09 million) fine on the German car maker as part of a global emissions cheating scandal and a regulator launched a civil lawsuit against a unit.
headline_main: Volkswagen Takes One-Two Punch in Australia With Fine, Lawsuit
headline_print_headline: Volkswagen Takes One-Two Punch in Australia With Fine, Lawsuit

abstract: A year-end rally in global equity markets extended gains on Friday, helped by data showing relatively strong U.S. growth, while sterling posted its worst week in more than two years on concerns over how Britain will leave the European Union.
snippet: A year-end rally in global equity markets extended gains on Friday, helped by data showing relatively strong U.S. growth, while sterling posted its worst week in more than two years on concerns over how Britain will leave the European Union.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A year-end rally in global equity markets extended gains on Friday, helped by data showing relatively strong U.S. growth, while sterling posted its worst week in more than two years on concerns over how Britain will leave the European Union.
headline_main: Stocks Extend Record Rally, Sterling Endures Rough Week
headline_print_headline: Stocks Extend Record Rally, Sterling Endures Rough Week

abstract: In 24 hours, the global event brand Elrow whisked in and out of Brooklyn with its art and music extravaganza.
snippet: In 24 hours, the global event brand Elrow whisked in and out of Brooklyn with its art and music extravaganza.
lead_paragraph: Things were running smoothly until a 12-foot aluminum tree collapsed and 30 colored orbs the size of bowling balls rolled toward the edge of the stage that had been erected a mere 10 hours earlier.
headline_main: Watch an Empty Warehouse Become a Psychedelic Party Wonderland

abstract: The police killed an average of 17 people every day in Brazil last year, and rogue officers are killing even more off duty. “I’m a hero to my people,” one militia leader said.
snippet: The police killed an average of 17 people every day in Brazil last year, and rogue officers are killing even more off duty. “I’m a hero to my people,” one militia leader said.
lead_paragraph: BELÉM, Brazil — The masked gunmen pulled up to Wanda’s Bar at 3:49 p.m. on May 19 and began firing the moment they left their vehicles. Two people, including Wanda herself, died on the patio.

abstract: Nearly 40 percent of pregnant surgery residents consider dropping out. Many wonder: Why can’t the system accommodate motherhood?
snippet: Nearly 40 percent of pregnant surgery residents consider dropping out. Many wonder: Why can’t the system accommodate motherhood?
lead_paragraph: As a health care professional, Dr. Erika Rangel is trained to know when things are going wrong. That alarm went off one day in her fourth year of surgical residency. Her son, just 3 months old, had developed a fever. She couldn’t be late for her operating shift, but his day care wouldn’t accept him if he was sick. So she did what desperate mothers do and got inventive: She slipped liquid Tylenol into his bottle, in the hopes of lowering his temperature, and dropped him off.

abstract: An Indian court sentenced a lawmaker from the governing party on Friday to life in prison after finding him guilty of abducting and raping a minor girl in 2017.
snippet: An Indian court sentenced a lawmaker from the governing party on Friday to life in prison after finding him guilty of abducting and raping a minor girl in 2017.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — An Indian court sentenced a lawmaker from the governing party on Friday to life in prison after finding him guilty of abducting and raping a minor girl in 2017.
headline_main: Indian Court Jails Lawmaker for Life in Rape of Minor
headline_print_headline: Indian Court Jails Lawmaker for Life in Rape of Minor

abstract: For more than 50 years, the charismatic restaurateur has been in business. His one day off? Christmas.
snippet: For more than 50 years, the charismatic restaurateur has been in business. His one day off? Christmas.
lead_paragraph: In a small building on East 57th Street, nestled among residential towers and far from most of the area’s commercial bustle, is an escape hatch from New York strife called Neary’s. Inside this upscale Irish pub is a peaceful cove of red banquettes, white-haired bartenders and an unchanging menu of conventional surf and turf.
